The story (serial and/or feature) deals with the plotting of a European importing firm to put Chinese trade competition in a west coast Chinatown - city unnamed, but it's by the bay and it isn't Oakland - out of business. Their representative, Sonya Rokoff/The Dragon Lady, a beautiful Eurasian girl, hires Victor Poten, a mad Eurasian chemist and inventor and an equal-opportunity racist who hates both Chinese and White races, to aid her. Poten, by means of his infernal inventions and underworld henchmen, conducts successful raids on the Chinese merchants and also successfully eludes the people hunting and investigating him. Those include newspaper reporter Joan Whiting, her sweetheart Martin Andrews, Willy Fu, Martin's servant, and police Captain Walters and his detectives. After narrow escapes from death in the form of bombs, poison-traps, infernal machines and some hand-to-hand, five-on-one scuffling in Chinatown's underworld, Martin finally captures Poten just as he is about to indulge in a little wholesale killing by poisoning the wine served at a Chinese merchant's banquet. description: The documentary is about Daniel Negreanu, a Canadian professional poker player who has won six World Series of Poker (WSOP) bracelets and two World Poker Tour (WPT) championship titles.

title: Fast Girls
description: The film tracks the rollercoaster journey of a British female sprint relay team, mainly centers on a talented runner from a rough part of London who joins the team and races for glory at the World Championships.

title: Going to the Mat
description: Jace Newfield has a problem. Besides being blind and being the new kid at school, his problem is that the kids at his new school thinks he’s a jerk. So in an effort to fit in, he tries out for the wrestling team and becomes a high-school wrestler.

title: Hard Times
description: The movie centers on Chaney, a drifter who travels to Louisiana during the Great Depression and begins competing in illegal bare-knuckled boxing matches. As his partner is drowning in debts, Chaney must fight hard to save him.

title: Who's Your Caddy?
description: This comedy stars Big Boi as C-Note, a celebrated rap mogul who is denied membership into an exclusive country club in the Hamptons. Undeterred, C-Note gets the brilliant idea to buy the land adjacent to the golf club's 17th hole, which he cleverly leverages to gain membership.

89 tells the incredible story of one of football’s greatest triumphs: when against all odds Arsenal snatched the Championship title from Liverpool at Anfield in the last minute of the last game of the 1988/89 season. Let's enjoy the movie!

title: Amateur
description: This movie follows 14-year-old basketball phenom Terron Forte as he has to navigate the under-the-table world of amateur athletics when he is recruited to an elite NCAA prep school.

title: Chasing Evel: The Robbie Knievel Story
description: The movie is based on the life and career of Evel Knievel’s son Robbie who was the most celebrated daredevil in the 80s and 90s. His life is uncovered through his personal pursuit of sobriety and the need of continuing his father's legacy by jumping once again.

title: Blood and Glory
description: Inspired by true events during the Anglo-Boer War, the movie follows Willem Morkel, a Boer and family man whose wife and son are murdered. Captured as a prisoner of war, Willem must survive incarceration in the notorious St. Helena concentration camp and defeat the ruthless Colonel Swannell.
